{
  "id": "5f39f5e0c46756ca",
  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/skelar/1ebbc3b2-a8b6-4b2b-8980-57986cd6ffb2/application",
    "company": "skelar",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "5f39f5e0c46756ca",
    "department": "Product",
    "description": "[https://app.ashbyhq.com/api/images/user-content/586ac3cb-f234-40cf-96fd-3daae8c41309/3a2721ac-0cf6-4bb5-a785-483b8d1018c3/Ashby_header.png]\n\nHi! We are Liven. We develop a global ecosystem of products that help people gain self-observability and steer away from negative thoughts, patterns, and behaviors on their personal journey.\n\nOur UX Research team is the compass of our product development. We don’t rely on assumptions; we dive deep into real user insights to guide our decisions. As we scale, we are looking for two UX Researchers to join our mission. This is a perfect starting point for those looking to pivot into IT and build a meaningful career in UX Research within a product-driven environment.\n\nImportant! Given the requirement for frequent interaction with users, the core working hours for this role will typically be 14:00 to 22:00.\n\n\n\n🎯 HOW WILL YOU MAKE AN IMPACT?\n\n - End-to-end Research: Participate in the full UX research cycle under the mentorship of our Lead UX Researcher — from defining research questions to presenting actionable insights.\n\n - Qualitative Exploration: Assist in planning and conducting user interviews, usability testing, concept testing, and discovery research.\n\n - Data Synthesis: Work with quantitative data, analyzing survey results and behavioral metrics alongside our analytics team.\n\n - Insight Generation: Transform raw data into structured insights and clear product recommendations.\n\n - Market Intelligence: Conduct desk research and competitive analysis to identify new growth opportunities for our ecosystem.\n\n - Hypothesis Testing: Learn to formulate research hypotheses and help product teams validate them through rigorous testing.\n\n - Continuous Growth: Rapidly immerse yourself in new domains, decode user behavior, and sharpen your research expertise through constant feedback.\n\n\n🧩 WHAT MAKES YOU A PERFECT FIT?\n\n - Language Proficiency: English at a C1 level or higher (most of our research and internal communication happens in English).\n\n - Academic background: A degree in Sociology, Psychology, Economics, or related fields.\n\n - Previous experience: You have experience in any type of research (sociological, psychological, academic, or marketing).\n\n - Analytical Mindset: Strong critical thinking skills with the ability to question assumptions and identify cause-and-effect relationships.\n\n - Information Management: Ability to process, structure, and synthesize large volumes of information.\n\n - Empathy \u0026 Curiosity: A genuine interest in human behavior, motivations, and decision-making processes.\n\n - Agility: Readiness to learn fast, embrace constructive feedback, and adapt to a high-paced environment.\n\n - Communication: Ability to clearly articulate thoughts and argue conclusions based on evidence.\n\n\n🌱 EVEN BETTER IF YOU:\n\n - Possess a background in marketing, market research, or research agencies.\n\n - Understand the basic principles of UX, product management, or customer experience.\n\n - Are a \"switcher\" who has proactively mastered the basics of the UX Research profession.\n\n\n💪🏻 WHAT WILL YOU ENJOY MOST ABOUT BEING AT LIVEN?\n\n - Culture of Curiosity: A place for explorers who embrace the unknown and achieve stellar results even when there’s no playbook.\n\n - Growth through Impact: Your professional evolution is directly tied to the value you bring to the product and the business.\n\n - Global Impact: Develop a product that supports the mental well-being of millions of users worldwide every day.\n\n - Trust and Ownership: The freedom to act, coupled with high responsibility for the outcome.\n\n - Expert Community: Access to professional clubs, specialized training, a knowledge base, and a library for your continuous learning.\n\n - Space for Focus: Autonomous offices in Kyiv and Warsaw with breakfasts, lunches, lounge areas, and wellness zones.\n\n - Well-being Program: We care about the mental health of our team as much as we care about our users, including medical insurance and sports communities.\n\n - Support during the war: We provide conditions for stable work and contribute to Ukraine's recovery through the SKELAR foundation.\n\nStill on Day 1: A Constant Expedition We keep the \"Day 1\" spirit — constantly asking questions, testing hypotheses, and adapting. If you are driven by curiosity and want to help users understand themselves better through research, let’s connect.\n\nFuel your curiosity at Liven 🔎\n\n[https://app.ashbyhq.com/api/images/user-content/586ac3cb-f234-40cf-96fd-3daae8c41309/bf8afb62-59f5-436b-b500-74f06bd0bb6e/Ashby_footer_eng.png]",
